What are presumptuous acts?
By definition, when someone rashly or impertinently does something that he is not authorized to do, he is acting presumptuously.
Because of inherited sin, we all act presumptuously at times.
But as King Saul’s example illustrates, if we develop a pattern of pushing ahead, sooner or later we will find ourselves in serious trouble with God.
says of Jehovah: You rebuke the presumptuous.
Why is that?
Presumptuous acts are more serious than innocent mistakes.
First, when we act immodestly, we fail to honor Jehovah as our rightful Sovereign.
Second, if we act beyond the scope of our authority, we are likely to get into conflict with others.
And third, when it becomes clear that we have acted presumptuously, we may be embarrassed or even humiliated.
Presumptuous acts do not turn out well.
As the Scriptures show, modesty is always the right course.
